  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word '\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935' (Bhedbhaav) means discrimination or prejudice. It refers to the unjust or prejudicial treatment of different categories of people, especially on the grounds of race, age, sex, religion, caste, or disability. The word is composed of two parts:\n\n1. '\u092d\u0947\u0926' (Bhed) - meaning difference or distinction\n2. '\u092d\u093e\u0935' (Bhaav) - meaning feeling or attitude\n\nWhen combined, '\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935' describes the act of treating people differently or unfairly based on their inherent characteristics or group memberships.",
